VALUES
(42, 3, 5, 23, 42, 16, 16, 'the crooked shall be made straight', 'Connection of Straight Paths', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of making crooked things straight. This connection highlights the transformative work of God in guiding people along new paths.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 5, 26, 17, 24, 24, 'brought low', 'Elevation and Humbling Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the reversal of status, where high things are brought low and low things are exalted. This connection highlights the transformative power of God in altering the landscape of existence.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 5, 58, 12, 12, 13, 'made straight', 'Paths and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of making straight paths. Luke speaks of making the crooked straight, while Hebrews encourages making straight paths for your feet, suggesting a theme of preparation and healing.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 5, 42, 1, 51, 53, 'every mountain and hill shall be brought low', 'Connection of Humility and Exaltation', 'This connection highlights the theme of reversal, where the proud and mighty are brought low, paralleling the imagery of valleys being filled and mountains brought low. Both passages emphasize the transformation of social order and the elevation of the humble.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 5, 59, 1, 9, 9, 'every valley shall be filled', 'Exaltation of the Lowly', 'This connection highlights the theme of elevation and humility. In Luke, the valleys are filled and the lowly are raised, while in James, the brother of low degree is encouraged to rejoice in his exaltation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 23, 52, 10, 10, 'all flesh shall see the salvation of God', 'Connection of Salvation in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize that all nations will see the salvation of God. This connection highlights a shared theme of universal revelation of God''s salvation.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 23, 40, 5, 5, 'all flesh shall see', 'Connection of Salvation and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize that ''all flesh shall see'' the revelation of God''s glory and salvation. This connection highlights the universal scope of God''s promise as articulated in both texts.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 19, 98, 2, 3, 'all flesh shall see the salvation of God', 'Connection of Salvation Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the visibility of God''s salvation to all people. Luke 3:6 states that ''all flesh shall see the salvation of God,'' while Psalms 98:2-3 declares that ''all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 45, 10, 18, 18, 'salvation of God', 'Salvation and Universal Reach', 'Both passages emphasize the universal nature of God''s salvation. Luke 3:6 speaks of all flesh seeing salvation, while Romans 10:18 highlights that their sound went into all the earth.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 42, 2, 10, 11, 'salvation of God', 'Salvation and Good Tidings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation being available to all people. Luke 3:6 states that ''all flesh shall see the salvation of God,'' while Luke 2:10-11 announces the birth of a Savior for ''all people.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 42, 2, 30, 32, 'salvation of God', 'Connection of Salvation Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of salvation being visible to all people. Luke 3:6 states that ''all flesh shall see the salvation of God,'' while Luke 2:30-32 expresses that salvation has been prepared for ''all people.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 6, 45, 10, 12, 12, 'all flesh shall see the salvation of God', 'Universal Salvation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusivity of God''s salvation. Luke 3:6 speaks of ''all flesh'' seeing salvation, while Romans 10:12 highlights that there is ''no difference between the Jew and the Greek.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 40, 23, 33, 33, 'O generation of vipers', 'Connection of Viper Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''generation of vipers,'' highlighting a shared condemnation of the people addressed. This connection underscores a consistent theme of warning against impending judgment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 40, 12, 34, 34, 'O generation of vipers', 'Connection of ''Generation of Vipers''', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''O generation of vipers'', highlighting a condemnation of evil. This connection illustrates a shared theme of moral judgment and the nature of the heart''s intentions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 52, 1, 10, 10, 'wrath to come', 'Connection of Wrath to Come', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''wrath to come.'' Luke 3:7 warns about fleeing from this wrath, while 1 Thessalonians 1:10 speaks of Jesus delivering believers from it. This connection highlights a shared theme of impending judgment and deliverance.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 1, 3, 15, 15, 'wrath to come', 'Enmity and Wrath Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of conflict, as both passages address enmity and impending judgment. The ''wrath to come'' in Luke reflects the consequences of sin, similar to the enmity described in Genesis.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 19, 58, 4, 5, 'generation of vipers', 'Connection of Serpent Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of serpents and poison, highlighting the danger posed by those who do not heed warnings. The ''generation of vipers'' in Luke parallels the ''poison of a serpent'' in Psalms, suggesting a shared theme of deceit and danger.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 23, 59, 5, 5, 'generation of vipers', 'Connection of Vipers Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of vipers, linking the idea of danger and death associated with them. In Luke, John the Baptist warns the crowd about the ''generation of vipers,'' while Isaiah speaks of the lethal consequences of consuming viper eggs.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 7, 58, 6, 18, 18, 'flee from the wrath to come', 'Fleeing from Wrath and Seeking Refuge', 'This connection highlights the theme of fleeing from impending danger. In Luke, the multitude is warned to flee from ''the wrath to come,'' while Hebrews speaks of those who have ''fled for refuge'' to find hope.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 26, 18, 27, 31, 'fruits worthy of repentance', 'Repentance and Transformation', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of repentance and the transformation of one''s heart and actions. Luke 3:8''s call for ''fruits worthy of repentance'' parallels Ezekiel 18:31''s urging to ''make you a new heart and a new spirit.''', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 44, 26, 20, 20, 'fruits worthy of repentance', 'Repentance and Works Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of repentance and the corresponding actions that demonstrate it. Luke 3:8 speaks of ''fruits worthy of repentance,'' while Acts 26:20 mentions ''works meet for repentance,'' highlighting a thematic link between repentance and tangible deeds.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 23, 1, 16, 18, 'fruits worthy of repentance', 'Call to Repentance and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the need for genuine repentance and moral action. Luke 3:8''s call for ''fruits worthy of repentance'' parallels Isaiah 1:16-18''s directive to ''put away the evil of your doings.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 48, 5, 22, 24, 'fruits worthy of repentance', 'Fruits of Repentance and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of ''fruits'' in both passages. Luke emphasizes producing ''fruits worthy of repentance,'' while Galatians lists the ''fruit of the Spirit,'' suggesting a continuity in the idea of demonstrating genuine faith through actions.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 40, 21, 43, 43, 'fruits worthy of repentance', 'Fruits of Repentance and Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of producing ''fruits'' as a requirement for inheriting the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the necessity of genuine repentance and the consequences of failing to produce such fruits.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 58, 6, 7, 8, 'fruits worthy of repentance', 'Fruits of Repentance and Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of producing good outcomes, whether through ''fruits worthy of repentance'' or ''herbs meet for them.'' They highlight the consequences of failing to bear good fruit, leading to rejection or cursing.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 8, 6, 4, 3, 8, 'God is able of these stones', 'Connection of Stones and Repentance', 'This connection highlights the theme of God using stones to signify His power and purpose. In Luke, God can raise up children from stones, while in Joshua, stones serve as a memorial of God''s miraculous act, emphasizing the importance of recognizing God''s work.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 9, 40, 7, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Good Fruit and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the consequence of not producing good fruit, indicating that such trees will be hewn down and cast into the fire. This thematic parallel underscores the urgency of bearing good fruit in one''s life.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 9, 43, 15, 6, 6, 'cast into the fire', 'Judgment and Consequences of Fruitlessness', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of not producing good fruit, illustrating a theme of judgment. The imagery of being cast into the fire connects the fate of unfruitful trees and branches.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 9, 42, 13, 9, 9, 'bringeth not forth good fruit', 'Fruitfulness and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of bearing good fruit, linking the idea of judgment to fruitlessness. The consequences of not producing fruit are similarly severe in both verses.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 3, 9, 23, 10, 33, 34, 'hewn down', 'Judgment and Humbling Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment against those who do not produce good fruit or exhibit humility. The imagery of being hewn down and cut down connects the consequences of failing to meet divine expectations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
